        <num>CC 3483</num>
        <heading>3483.  Just title</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3483.  Just title
A just title is a juridical act, such as a sale, exchange, or donation, sufficient to transfer ownership or another real right.  The act must be written, valid in form, and filed for registry in the conveyance records of the parish in which the immovable is situated.</p>
        </content>
